B.Matplotlib,Arrays

1.
*Creating bar graph using Matplotlib and arrays as python libraries

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
x=np.array(['A','B','C','D'])
y=np.array([10,20,30,40])
plt.bar(x, y,)
plt.xlabel('time')
plt.suptitle('the rise')
plt.show()


2.
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

import numpy as np           
x=np.random.randint(0,10,size=(10))
y=np.random.randint(0,10,size=(10))
color=np.random.randint(10,size=(10))
plt.scatter(x, y, c=color)
plt.colorbar()
plt.show()
